By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has reported 410 new cases of COVID-19 Tuesday, with the national caseload now a touch away from the 50,000 mark. According to the report released via twitter handle, Lagos topped with 210 cases, more than 50 percent of the total recorded cases for all the other 15 states. Sundiata Post recalls that Lagos also logged 207 of the 417 cases reported on Monday, a sign that the virus is still potent in Nigeria’s commercial capital. FCT Abuja reported 45 cases, while Ondo has 30. The number of COVID-19 patients treated and discharged increased from 337 on Monday to 554. Four deaths were reported in the 24 hour cycle, taking the death toll to 981 See the details below: Lagos-210 FCT-45 Ondo-30 Plateau-21 Edo-19 Ogun-16 Oyo-13 Nasarawa-12 Bauchi-11 Enugu-10 Kwara-7 Kaduna-6 Anambra-4 Ebonyi-3 Abia-2 Rivers-1 49,895 confirmed 37,051 discharged 981 deaths  By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The Federal Capital territory has beating Lagos again on the leaderboard with 90 infections as the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control confirms 304 new cases of COVID-19 in Nigeria. COVID-19 cases in Nigeria are plateauing as the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control logged… August 5, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuk Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The reported cases of COVID-19 infections Thursday shrunk to 373 compared to the 473 cases recorded on Wednesday, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control report has shown. However, there was a reported increase in death toll from 956 the previous day (Wednesday) to… August 14, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has announced the confirmation of 453 new cases of COVID-19 infections just as it reported that a total of 33,044 patients have been treated and discharged in Nigeria since the index case in February 27, 2020. Disclosing… August 9, 2020 In "News"